      "solution": "(d) According to given letters codes\n1 6 3 5 1 4 9 7 8 4 2\nF L O U R = x n c a p\nA N I M A L W O R L D\n\nSolutions (Q. Nos. 2-6)\nGiven that, F L O U R = x n c a p ...(i)\nT A P = k s d ...(ii)\nR O S E = c m r n ...(iii)\nL O T U S = s m c p x ...(iv)\nS A I L = k p t m ...(v)\n\nFrom Eqs. (ii) and (v),\nT A P = k s d\nS A I L = c p t m\n∴ A = k\nFrom Eqs. (ii) and (iv),\nT A P = k s d\nL O T U S = s m c p x\n∴ T = s ⇒ P = d\nFrom (iii) and (v),\nR O S E = c m r n\nS A I L = k p t m\n∴ S = m\n\nFrom Eqs. (iv) and (v),\nL O T U S = s m c p x\nS A I L = k p t m\n∴ L = P ⇒ l = t\nFrom Eqs. (iii) and (iv),\nR O S E = c m r n\nL O T U S = s m c p x\n∴ O = c, U = x\nFrom Eqs. (i) and (iii),\nF L O U R = x n t a p\nR O S E = c m r n\n∴ R = n, E = r, F = a\nNow, as per the given information, code of each letter is as below\n\n2. (c) Clearly, the code for F is a.\n3. (d) Clearly, the code for P is d.\n4. (d) Clearly, the code for L is p."
